---
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---
<BaseLayout title="YouTube sync">
  <h1>YouTube sync</h1>

  <p>Auto-imports new sermons from a configured YouTube channel.</p>
  <h2>Setup</h2>
  <p>Site Settings → Integrations → YouTube. Set <em>YouTubeChannelId</em> + <em>YouTubeApiKey</em> (Google Cloud Console; YouTube Data API v3).</p>
  <h2>Behavior</h2>
  <p>The YouTubeSyncService background worker polls the channel hourly. New videos become draft Sermons (manual review + publish required). Includes title, description, thumbnail, publishedAt.</p>
  <h2>Rate limits</h2>
  <p>YouTube API has a daily quota (~10,000 units). The poll uses ~3 units per call. Hourly polling is well within the free tier.</p>
  <h2>Manual sync</h2>
  <p>From Site Settings → Integrations → YouTube → "Sync now" button forces an immediate poll outside the hourly tick.</p>
</BaseLayout>
